Reference domain.

The bank has three principal groups consuming the data, and they're the lens for this whole notebook.

Analysts see aggregated gold tables, but not raw sensitive data — no email, phone, or date of birth. Fraud analysts see masked card numbers — say the last four digits — and can read the silver layer. And the compliance group sees full sensitive data, but only for the regions they're responsible for.

So three groups, three different views of the same tables. Every governance feature we cover — grants, masks, row filters, attribute-based policies — exists to make those three views true at the same time, over one shared set of tables.
